{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":33429,"name":"Teknologicus","username":"Teknologicus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/teknologicus/{size}/2646_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-04T12:40:53.539Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHow does one control the distance at which a transparent material (texture with apha channel) becomes opaque vs. maintains transparency?  Here’s my material:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAlpha.xml\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"Textures/texture_atlas.dds\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDo I need to define a custom technique for this material, and if so, what parameter(s) would I set?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-04T12:40:53.539Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":46,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":240.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"Teknologicus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1063,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33436,"name":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-04T19:23:10.954Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou can add multiple techniques to a single material and assign a \u003ccode\u003eloddistance\u003c/code\u003e to them. This determines the distance (divided by the scale I believe) at which each technique is used.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you’re interested about adding LODs to your models as well; I made a video about that:\u003c/p\u003e\u003caside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"2083\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/40/3290_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/information-source-how-to-exporting-lods-with-blender/2083\"\u003e\u003cimg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/information_source.png?v=10\" title=\"information_source\" alt=\"information_source\" class=\"emoji\"\u003e How to: Exporting LODs with Blender\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca class=\"badge-wrapper  bullet\" href=\"/c/showcase/artists/14\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-parent-bg\" style=\"background-color: #F1592A;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"badge-category-bg\" style=\"background-color: #8C6238;\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category clear-badge\" title=\"Discuss Urho3D art-related topics (creation, import, export, troubleshooting) and share your free art.\"\u003eArtists\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cblockquote\u003e\n    \n  \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-04T19:25:15.663Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":37,"readers_count":36,"score":27.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/information-source-how-to-exporting-lods-with-blender/2083","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":":information_source: How to: Exporting LODs with Blender","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33440,"name":"Teknologicus","username":"Teknologicus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/teknologicus/{size}/2646_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-05T00:48:15.197Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI tried the below but it doesn’t seem to make any visual difference.  I’ve attached a screenshot with this material active for the water to show what I’m seeing.  Each terrain cube is 1 unit in size.  I’m not sure what I’m doing wrong. \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/face_with_raised_eyebrow.png?v=9\" title=\":face_with_raised_eyebrow:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":face_with_raised_eyebrow:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAlpha.xml\" quality=\"2\" loddistance=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAlpha.xml\" quality=\"1\" loddistance=\"128\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAlpha.xml\" quality=\"0\" loddistance=\"256\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"Textures/texture_atlas.dds\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/1/14212bbc78917ce95dc0e8816001cb640acede0c.png\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/2S4Ci77PDtTT82fsMAnJkmPI8m8.png?dl=1\" title=\"Untitled.png\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/14212bbc78917ce95dc0e8816001cb640acede0c_2_690x407.png\" alt=\"Untitled\" data-base62-sha1=\"2S4Ci77PDtTT82fsMAnJkmPI8m8\" width=\"690\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/14212bbc78917ce95dc0e8816001cb640acede0c_2_690x407.png, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/14212bbc78917ce95dc0e8816001cb640acede0c_2_1035x610.png 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/14212bbc78917ce95dc0e8816001cb640acede0c_2_1380x814.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/1/14212bbc78917ce95dc0e8816001cb640acede0c_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eUntitled.png\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1680×991 639 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eP.S.  I also tried the below with same results.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAlpha.xml\" quality=\"2\" loddistance=\"64\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAlpha.xml\" quality=\"1\" loddistance=\"128\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAlpha.xml\" quality=\"0\" loddistance=\"256\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"Textures/texture_atlas.dds\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-05T00:59:56.313Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":31,"readers_count":30,"score":16.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"Teknologicus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/1/14212bbc78917ce95dc0e8816001cb640acede0c.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"14212bbc78917ce95dc0e8816001cb640acede0c.png","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Modanung","name":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1063,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33441,"name":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-05T07:06:10.912Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWell yes, you’re using the same technique three times. \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slightly_smiling_face.png?v=9\" title=\":slightly_smiling_face:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slightly_smiling_face:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nTry something that looks more like:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAlpha.xml\" quality=\"0\" loddistance=\"0\"  /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/Diff.xml\"      quality=\"0\" loddistance=\"32\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m not sure how the \u003cem\u003equality\u003c/em\u003e works, but I guess it allows you to link your material to graphics settings.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-05T22:34:50.663Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":21.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"username":"Teknologicus","name":"Teknologicus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/teknologicus/{size}/2646_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33443,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-09-05T13:31:03.338Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIs there problem that you don’t want the water to appear transparent further from the camera? If so, what happens if you disable mip mapping on your texture atlas?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf I remember correctly (I may be entirely wrong) mip mapping sometimes doesn’t play nicely with texture atlases/transparency, though someone else may be able to provide better advice.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-06T00:05:37.483Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":28,"readers_count":27,"score":25.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Teknologicus","name":"Teknologicus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/teknologicus/{size}/2646_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33449,"name":"Vitalii","username":"restless","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/r/3da27b/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-09-05T17:57:46.943Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI used similar technique for distant foliage. At distance tree leaves and grass would fully disappear due to how mip maps work… So I just made the last mip level part fully opaque \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e Worked surprisingly well\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-07T19:27:11.788Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":28,"readers_count":27,"score":20.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"Vitalii","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"SirNate0","name":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1183,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33454,"name":"Teknologicus","username":"Teknologicus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/teknologicus/{size}/2646_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-06T00:10:41.433Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThank you to everyone that replied.  It was indeed a mipmap issue, and once I eliminated and disabled mipmaps for the water texture, it looks as desired.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/6/6cd8c3be9c3b2e30696cd9fca1beed3f92897dc9.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/fwTYWbWcbd4JicqgtGcXSIQnja9.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"Untitled.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/6/6cd8c3be9c3b2e30696cd9fca1beed3f92897dc9.jpeg\" alt=\"Untitled\" data-base62-sha1=\"fwTYWbWcbd4JicqgtGcXSIQnja9\" width=\"690\" height=\"407\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/6/6cd8c3be9c3b2e30696cd9fca1beed3f92897dc9_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eUntitled.jpg\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e840×496 243 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eP.S.  I got to playing with the code from Urho3D’s water sample (23_water) and did this.  It doesn’t play nice with my code yet (water at different depths than sea level, no water at sea level, etc.), but looks very cool in a test run!\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lazyYT\" data-youtube-id=\"3O1iqVnGzUM\" data-youtube-title=\"Fancy Water\" data-width=\"480\" data-height=\"270\" data-parameters=\"feature=oembed\u0026amp;wmode=opaque\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-06T01:16:24.392Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":40.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"Teknologicus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3O1iqVnGzUM","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"YouTube","clicks":0},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/6/6cd8c3be9c3b2e30696cd9fca1beed3f92897dc9.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"6cd8c3be9c3b2e30696cd9fca1beed3f92897dc9.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1063,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33455,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-09-06T02:35:03.104Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eSince it does seem to be a mipmap problem and you seem to be using a dds file for the texture already you may want to simply edit the higher mipmaps by hand to fix the transparency while retaining the benefits of using mipmaps. I’m pretty sure GIMP can do this if you don’t already have tools that will.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-06T02:35:03.104Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":15.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Teknologicus","name":"Teknologicus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/teknologicus/{size}/2646_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33456,"name":"Teknologicus","username":"Teknologicus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/teknologicus/{size}/2646_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-06T03:15:35.154Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAgreed.  I definitely want to use a texture atlas with mipmap for as much of the terrain as possible to avoid that pixel shimmer one gets without mipmaps.  With water and glass I will use a texture atlas without the mipmaps and see how that goes (I haven’t tested the glass texture yet).  For blocks with transparent areas and opaque blocks I will use the texture atlas with mipmaps.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI develop under Linux and do use GIMP for the dds file stuff.  I also wrote a custom mipmap generator for my texture atlases that doesn’t blend tiles across each other.  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-06T03:15:35.154Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":50.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"Teknologicus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"SirNate0","name":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1063,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":33535,"name":"Teknologicus","username":"Teknologicus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/teknologicus/{size}/2646_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-07T19:26:59.084Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI found a solution for the texture atlas mipmap generation and alpha channel which works both with tiles like leaves and grass which only contain pixel alpha values of 255 or 0 (with the textures I’m using \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/cylgom/freeture\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/cylgom/freeture\u003c/a\u003e) and tiles like water and glass which have pixel alpha values somewhere in between 255 and 0:  When blending four pixels to make one pixel in a lower detail mipmap level, take the highest alpha value from the four pixels and use that as the result alpha value.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFollow up:  Averaging pixels (including alpha channel) for only pixels with alpha greater than zero works better for both partially transparent blocks and fully transparent blocks in my findings when generating mipmaps.  Now everything including water, ice, leaves can use the same texture altlas with mipmaps in my project.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-10T07:10:56.730Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":35.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":5549,"topic_slug":"transparent-material-and-opacity-distance","display_username":"Teknologicus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/cylgom/freeture","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - cylgom/freeture: WTFPL licensed faithful 16x16 minecraft texturepack","clicks":4}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1063,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true}],"stream":[33429,33436,33440,33441,33443,33449,33454,33455,33456,33535]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,1176],[2,1175],[6,1174],[10,1172]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7178,"title":"Medium-Quality Technique for Semi-Reflective/Specular Glass in Urho","fancy_title":"Medium-Quality Technique for Semi-Reflective/Specular Glass in Urho","slug":"medium-quality-technique-for-semi-reflective-specular-glass-in-urho","posts_count":3,"reply_count":0,"highest_post_numb